OL,3,CThe Welsh boxer banned from competing
OL,4,Cfor British title because he was black
OL,6,FCuthbert Taylor was a boxing pioneer
OL,7,Fin the 1920s and '30s. He was the
OL,8,Ffirst black boxer to represent Great
OL,9,FBritain at the Olympic Games in 1928.
OL,10,FHowever, he never had the chance to be
OL,11,Frecognised as the best in Britain.
OL,13,FThe British Boxing Board of Control
OL,14,Fbanned non-white boxers from competing
OL,15,Ffor the British title. The 'colour bar
OL,16,Frule', in place between 1911 and 1948,
OL,17,Fstated a fighter had to have two white
OL,18,Fparents.
